HIS FATHER THEN TOOK A JOB AS A CUSTODIAN AT THE WASHINGTON HEIGHTS LIBRARY IN NEW YORK
THEY GOT TO LIVE IN AN APARTMENT AT THE TOP OF THE LIBRARY WHICH WAS AT FIRST VERY EMBARRASSING TO MR CLARK
BUT THEN HE REALIZED IT WAS A BLESSING BECAUSE HE COULD READ AS MUCH AS HE WANTED AND SNEAK DOWNSTAIRS AT 3 AM
